    <steps>
        
        <step type="context" name="challengeYourself">
            <blocks>
                <block type="title">
                    <title id="JJJ-2S-9KA">A Sample Game</title>
                </block>
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="ziK-O11-sdfdfsee"><a href="playgrounds://currentdocument/UserModules/MyFiles.playgroundmodule/Sources/SampleLevel.swift"><icon name="module"/>  SampleLevel</a> is a completed version of the Brick Breaker game.</text>
                </block>
                <block type="text">
                        <text id="dWw-dp-Im1">You can learn a lot from reading code written by someone else. Try reading through <a href="playgrounds://currentdocument/UserModules/MyFiles.playgroundmodule/Sources/SampleLevel.swift"><icon name="module"/> SampleLevel</a> with these tips:</text>
                    </block>
                    <block type="text">
                        <text id="V4N-mB-MBg">1. Read the <a href="glossary://code%20comment">code comments</a> that explain the purpose of each function and variable.</text>
                    </block>
                    <block type="text">
                        <text id="33M-rB-2Ez">2. Try predicting what happens if you change a value or line of code. Then, <b>run your code</b> to see if you were right! If something unexpected happens, try to figure out why.</text>
                    </block>
                
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="ziK-ieieiqnvnvn-ssdfs">Run your code to see how it works!</text>
                </block>
                
            </blocks>
        </step>
        
        <message name="challengeYourself" sender="byte">
            <blocks>
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="wxX-nd-BG8">Want to keep building your game? Here are some additional things you can try:</text>
                </block>
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="VKD-AI-ibt">1. Add a score that you track across all of the levels, and display it after you win or lose.</text>
                </block>
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="2B2-sn-ikV">2. Create a moving brick that you need to destroy before it reaches the foul line.</text>
                </block>
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="aad-ve-wuj">3. Make an evasive brick that dodges the ball.</text>
                </block>
                <block type="text">
                    <text id="vrI-rh-aFX">4. Add “Impossible Mode” to the game.</text>
                </block>
            </blocks>
        </message>
    </steps>
</trail>
